commit_list.message:
tetris.cpp

add queue for user input...

lock queue from TetrisGameInfo

add drop, reward ADT and drop pool.
add QWUInevntory so that now can handle basic item move.
fix character decode for wvsgame wtih center

add item info manager.
fix wvslogin memory leak problem [ thread pointer not deleted ]
modify item list in GA_Character
[+] Channel will send it's information to Center when it connected on.
add field system, user class and mob, npc etc.
fix some bug, remove opcode to name.

add skill record decoding/encoding but should notice that the fourth job skills will cause 38 problem maybe caused by IsSkillNeedMasterLevel.
start working on basic stat but still in poor progress.

fix skill info failed loading some skills.
add shared packet instance for multi client packet async sending.

add Skill Factory (load skill data)
add exprtk : fast math expression parser for parsing skill attributes.
should note that skill factory work concurrently, watch out wz res release.

add attack parser so now user is able to attack mobs.
fix decoder for GW_SkillRecord.
add functions to deal with monster dead and monster hit.
Known bug: User must do some inventory operations to adjust the damage value (in status)

Working on temporary stat and basic stat, we now could test "Elemental Reset" skill.
Fixing monster not really spawned in the field ( or said, cant touch them ? like a ghost. )

Migrating some common libs into WvsLib.
Now monsters are able to give rewards.
Picking func fixed and RawAddItem fixed.
SP in stat is now worked.
Skill system basically woring on, you can up the skills.
Add another buff skill '2121052'.

ETC.

add save system.
fix lots of bugs including inventory manipluations and some core-side bug.
add functions to make item to GW_ItemSlotBase.
add simple command to drop item.
add item picking up funcs.

Fix memory leak caused by printf buffer.
Using 'new' for In/OutPacket  memory allocation instead of using Memory Pool (Will slow down the performance.)
Adding a simple algorithm for dropping the meso.
Implement QWUser funcs.
Implement some game messages packet (ex : DropPickedUp ... ).
Implement level up sys but not include Hp/Mp grow up.
Modify GW_Avatar, get Hair/Skin/Face from CharacterStat not from CharacterAvatar.

add lua script sys [test.lua in Release folder]
add quest fundamentals.

add new sql file.
remove some deprecated files.

add/modify some flags.
remove file "ClientPacketFlags".
fix mob controller's bugs.
keepalive of wvslogin still dead after a while (unknown reason).

add/fix some inventory operations.
modify the mechanism the WvsLogger used to improve the cpu usage(use cond variable instead of infinite loop forever).
add/modify basic quest system.
Changing wvsunified db class, using mysql pool instead of single db instance.
add WvsLogger inorder to improve debug performance.

Modify the folder hierarchy of project.
Fix some skills load failed.
Add light zip file of required library(poco and boost).
Remove some shit.

Modify the way designate the socket id.
Fix, again, keep center aliver.
Remove some useless stuffs.
Remove isConnected/isConnecting/isConnectionFailed, use SocketStatus instead.
Combine some functions(Connection relelated) to SocketBase.
Combine some functions(Set IP/Port) to WvsBase.
Rename some variables LEL.

Add temp status holder for channel transfer(also for shop I guess.).
Modify the channel entry and the way to record them.
Add WvsWorld.
User data now encode again by WvsGame because we need insert something after character data, we can't attach those packets or the client get 38.
Fix memory pool man crash because of initialization order not correct (Use GetInstance instead).
Update new sql file and script file.
WvsGame now have own channel id for transfer channel purpose(the Config files provided had been modified).

Add WvsShop project.
Now can get into shop but do nothing.
Can go back game server normally.
Extremely speed up the loading time of SkillInfo.

Fix WvsShop crashed after user leaved (caused by packet flag conflict.).
Fix Keep aliver of WvsShop/Login/Game stop working after a while when center disconnected.
